    <h2 id="service">Common Caliber Appliance Problems We Repair</h2>

    <p>We repair many of the issues homeowners commonly experience with <strong>Caliber appliances</strong>, from outdoor grill problems to refrigeration, wine, beverage, freezer, ice, griddle, and outdoor kitchen appliance concerns. Our service is tailored to the appliance type, model, installation style, outdoor exposure, and symptoms involved.</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Caliber grill not igniting:</strong> We diagnose ignition modules, electrodes, wiring, switches, gas supply symptoms, burner assemblies, and related components that affect proper startup.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber grill heating unevenly:</strong> If your grill has hot spots, weak flame, poor searing performance, or inconsistent heat distribution, we inspect burners, radiant systems, grill racks, valves, gas flow, airflow, and buildup that can affect cooking performance.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber Rockwell grill problems:</strong> We service supported Rockwell grill issues involving ignition, burners, heat output, lid movement, controls, grease management, uneven cooking, and performance decline.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber built-in grill issues:</strong> Built-in outdoor grills can be affected by clearance problems, ventilation restrictions, grease buildup, gas connection concerns, weather exposure, and installation-related airflow issues. We inspect the appliance and surrounding installation for proper performance.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber griddle performance problems:</strong> We diagnose supported griddle systems with uneven heating, ignition issues, grease management concerns, surface temperature problems, burner faults, and outdoor-use wear.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber outdoor refrigerator not cooling:</strong> We inspect airflow restrictions, condenser condition, evaporator fan issues, sensor faults, control issues, door sealing problems, compressor-related symptoms, and temperature regulation concerns.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber refrigerator drawer problems:</strong> If your refrigerator drawer is too warm, not closing properly, leaking, frosting, or making noise, we inspect drawer alignment, gaskets, fans, controls, sensors, airflow, and outdoor installation conditions.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber freezer drawer issues:</strong> We diagnose freezer drawers that are too warm, frosting, leaking, running constantly, not freezing properly, or experiencing door seal and airflow problems.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber wine cabinet temperature problems:</strong> Wine storage requires stable temperature control. We inspect sensors, fans, controls, door sealing, airflow, condenser performance, and cooling issues affecting wine storage conditions.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber beverage center not cooling:</strong> We diagnose beverage centers with warm temperatures, fan issues, door seal problems, control faults, condenser restrictions, noisy operation, and inconsistent cooling.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber beverage dispenser issues:</strong> We inspect cooling performance, dispensing problems, temperature irregularities, line concerns, airflow issues, and maintenance-related decline affecting supported beverage dispenser units.</li>

      <li><strong>Caliber clear ice machine problems:</strong> We diagnose poor ice production, no ice, cloudy ice, water flow issues, drain problems, pump concerns, sensor faults, scale buildup, and cleaning-related performance issues.</li>

      <li><strong>Door gasket and sealing issues:</strong> Proper sealing is important for outdoor refrigerators, freezer drawers, wine cabinets, beverage centers, and ice machines. We inspect worn gaskets, air leaks, water leaks, door alignment, hinge behavior, drawer alignment, and closure problems that affect performance.</li>

      <li><strong>Water leaks and drain issues:</strong> We diagnose blocked drains, condensation problems, ice machine drain faults, outdoor refrigerator leaks, water line concerns, and moisture problems inside or around the appliance.</li>

      <li><strong>Control and electrical faults:</strong> We service supported touch controls, displays, switches, sensors, wiring-related issues, error codes, temperature alarms, lighting controls, ignition controls, and electrical malfunctions affecting Caliber appliances.</li>

